lead_paragraph: A champion musher eyes an elite status, non-Alaska like weather continues to play havoc and competitors for the first time will carry cell or satellite phones in cases of emergencies. Those are among the highlights of the 2017 Iditarod as Alaska prepares to play host to the world's most famous sled dog race.
